Ľubomíra Kurhajcová.label: Lubomira Kurhajcova
Ľubomíra Kurhajcová.description: Ľubomíra Kurhajcová is a Slovak female professional tennis player. She reached her career high singles ranking of No. 59 on 24 May 2004. Wikipedia

Alexander Waske.label: Alexander Waske
Alexander Waske.description:
Alexander Waske is a retired professional tennis player from Germany.
Waske was ranked as high as World No. 16 in doubles, winning 4 titles. He achieved his career-high singles ranking of World No. 89 in June 2006. Wikipedia

Alla Kudryavtseva.label: Alla Kudryavtseva
Alla Kudryavtseva.description: Alla Alexandrovna Kudryavtseva is a professional tennis player from Russia. She currently lives in Moscow, where she is coached by Nick Rybakov. Wikipedia

Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi.label: Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi
Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi.description: Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi is a professional tennis player from Pakistan. He is currently Pakistan's top player. A top-10 doubles player, his highest singles ranking was no. 103. Wikipedia
Awards: Lux Style Award for Most Stylish Sportsperson

Amos Mansdorf.label: Amos Mansdorf
Amos Mansdorf.description:
Amos Mansdorf is a former Israeli professional tennis player.
His career-high singles ranking was World No. 18, the highest ever for any male Israeli tennis player. His career-high doubles ranking was World No. 67. Wikipedia

Althea Gibson.label: Althea Gibson
Althea Gibson.description: Althea Gibson was an American tennis player and professional golfer, and the first black athlete of either gender to cross the color line of international tennis. In 1956 she became the first person of color to win a Grand Slam title. Wikipedia
Althea Gibson.Born: August 25, 1927, Clarendon County, South Carolina, United States
Althea Gibson.Died: September 28, 2003, East Orange, New Jersey, United States
Awards: Associated Press Female Athlete of the Year

Alexander Vladimirovich Volkov.label: Alexander Vladimirovich Volkov
Alexander Vladimirovich Volkov.description: Alexander Vladimirovich Volkov is a former professional tennis player from Russia. Wikipedia

İpek Şenoğlu.label: İpek Şenoğlu
İpek Şenoğlu.description: İpek Şenoğlu, nicknamed İpeko, is a former Turkish tennis player. Şenoğlu first made history in June 2004 when she was accepted into the women's doubles qualifying for Wimbledon. Wikipedia

Aleksandra Krunić.label: Aleksandra Krunić
Aleksandra Krunić.description: Aleksandra Krunić is a Serbian professional tennis player, who was, as of 16 September 2012, ranked No. 126. Krunić has won six ITF events — five in singles and one in doubles. Wikipedia

Akiko Morigami.label: Akiko Morigami
Akiko Morigami.description: Akiko Morigami is a Japanese former professional tennis player. She turned professional in 1998. On August 15, 2005, Morigami reached her career-high singles ranking World No. 41. Wikipedia

Aiko Nakamura.label: Aiko Nakamura
Aiko Nakamura.description: Aiko Nakamura, is a female Japanese tennis player. She was once the second highest WTA-ranked Japanese singles tennis player, at 107, after Ai Sugiyama. Wikipedia

Anke Huber.label: Anke Huber
Anke Huber.description: Anke Huber is a German retired professional tennis player. She was the runner-up in women's singles at the 1996 Australian Open. Her career-high singles ranking was fourth, also in 1996. Wikipedia

Andreja Klepač.label: Andreja Klepač
Andreja Klepač.description:
Andreja Klepač is a professional Slovenian tennis player.
While she has not won a WTA title of any kind, she has won 3 ITF singles titles and 12 ITF doubles titles. Wikipedia

Anna Lapushchenkova.label: Anna Lapushchenkova
Anna Lapushchenkova.description: Anna Lapushchenkova is a Russian professional tennis player, since 2003. Wikipedia

Bernard Tomic.label: Bernard Tomic
Bernard Tomic.description: Bernard Tomic is an Australian professional tennis player who as of 13 January 2014 is ranked World No. 57 by the Association of Tennis Professionals. Wikipedia

Ayumi Morita.label: Ayumi Morita
Ayumi Morita.description: Ayumi Morita is a Japanese tennis player. She reached her career-high ranking of 42nd in the world on June 6, 2011 and is currently the second highest ranked Japanese player in the world at World No. 74, the seventh overall in Asia. Wikipedia

Bojana Bobusic.label: Bojana Bobusic
Bojana Bobusic.description: Bojana Bobusic is a former professional Australian tennis player playing on the ITF women's circuit. On 20 February 2012, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 227. She is coached by Rohan Fisher. Wikipedia

Art Larsen.label: Art Larsen
Art Larsen.description: Arthur David Larsen was an American No. 1 male tennis player best remembered for his victory at the U.S. Championships in 1950 and for his eccentricities. He won the "Times" national sports award for the outstanding tennis player of 1950. Wikipedia

Alicja Rosolska.label: Alicja Rosolska
Alicja Rosolska.description: Alicja Rosolska is a Polish professional tennis player ranked World No. 636 in singles and World No. 38 in doubles. Wikipedia

Chanelle Scheepers.label: Chanelle Scheepers
Chanelle Scheepers.description: Chanelle Scheepers is a South African professional tennis player. Her career high WTA singles ranking is No. 37, which she reached on 10 October 2011. Her career high doubles ranking is 82, set on 10 June 2013. Wikipedia
Chanelle Scheepers.Born: March 13, 1984 (age 30), Harrismith, Free State, South Africa

Beatriz García Vidagany.label: Beatriz García Vidagany
Beatriz García Vidagany.description: Beatriz García Vidagany is a Spanish tennis player. She reached a career high ranking of 166 in singles on the Sony Ericsson WTA Tour on June 7, 2010. Wikipedia

Carly Gullickson.label: Carly Gullickson
Carly Gullickson.description: Carly Gullickson is an former American professional tennis player. Her career-high WTA singles ranking is No. 123, which she reached on July 20, 2009. Her career high doubles ranking is No. 52, set at April 3, 2006. Wikipedia

Bob Bryan.label: Bob Bryan
Bob Bryan.description: Robert Charles "Bob" Bryan is an American male professional tennis player. He and his twin brother, Mike, are current world no. 1 doubles players and have spent over 290 weeks in this position. Wikipedia

Ashleigh Barty.label: Ashleigh Barty
Ashleigh Barty.description: Ashleigh Barty is an Australian professional tennis player, ranked number 13 in the world in doubles, and the youngest player in the top 20 doubles rankings. Wikipedia

Beatrice Capra.label: Beatrice Capra
Beatrice Capra.description: Beatrice "Trice" Capra is a professional American tennis player. Her highest WTA singles ranking is 201, which she reached on September 20, 2010. Her career high in doubles is 405, which she reached on July 4, 2011. Wikipedia
Beatrice Capra.Born: April 6, 1992 (age 21), Ellicott City, Maryland, United States

Bernd Karbacher.label: Bernd Karbacher
Bernd Karbacher.description: Bernd Karbacher is a professional German tennis player. His highest ATP singles ranking is World No. 22, which he reached on 17 April 1995. His career-high doubles ranking was World No. 163, achieved on 6 June 1994. Wikipedia

Chuang Chia-jung.label: Chuang Chia-jung
Chuang Chia-jung.description: Chuang Chia-jung is a Taiwanese professional female tennis player. In the Australian Open 2007, she reached the final of the women's doubles with her partner Chan Yung-jan, but lost in three sets to Cara Black and Liezel Huber. Wikipedia

Cyril Suk.label: Cyril Suk
Cyril Suk.description:
Cyril Suk III is a former professional tennis player. A doubles specialist, Suk won one Grand Slam men's doubles title and four Grand Slam mixed doubles titles during his career.
Suk comes from a prominent Czech tennis family. Wikipedia

Eleazar Davidman.label: Eleazar Davidman
Eleazar Davidman.description: Eleazar Davidman was a Jewish Israeli tennis player. Wikipedia

Camille Pin.label: Camille Pin
Camille Pin.description:
Camille Pin is a former professional French tennis player. Pin played right-handed and is 162 cm, or 5' 3¾" tall.
Camille's 2006 season was rather successful, for a player ranked lower than the top 100 in the women's tour. Wikipedia

Brian Teacher.label: Brian Teacher
Brian Teacher.description:
Brian David Teacher is a 6'3" right-handed American former professional male tennis player. He reached a career-high ranking World No. 7 in 1981.
Teacher is best remembered for his singles championship at the Australian Open in 1980. Wikipedia
Brian Teacher.Born: December 23, 1954 (age 59), San Diego, California, United States

Björn Phau.label: Björn Phau
Björn Phau.description: Björn Phau is a German tennis player. He reached a career-high singles ranking of World No. 59 in June 2006. He defeated Andre Agassi 7–5, 7–5 at the 2006 Dubai Tennis Championships. Wikipedia

David Rikl.label: David Rikl
David Rikl.description: David Rikl is a former professional tennis player from the Czech Republic. His success came mostly in doubles, winning 30 titles and finishing runner-up at the 2004 US Open and 2001 Wimbledon Championships Men's Doubles. Wikipedia
David Rikl.Born: February 27, 1971 (age 43), Brandýs nad Labem-Stará Boleslav, Czech Republic

Esther Vergeer.label: Esther Vergeer
Esther Vergeer.description: Esther Mary Vergeer is a retired Dutch wheelchair tennis player. Combining singles and doubles, she has won 42 Grand Slam tournaments, 22 year-end championships and 7 Paralympics titles. Wikipedia
Awards: Laureus World Sports Award for Sportsperson of the Year with a Disability
Nominations: Best Athlete with a Disability ESPY Award

Eric Jelen.label: Eric Jelen
Eric Jelen.description:
Eric Jelen is a former tennis player from Germany, who won one singles and five doubles titles during his professional career.
The right-hander Jelen reached his highest singles ATP-ranking on 7 July 1986, when he became World No. 23. Wikipedia

Eva Hrdinová.label: Eva Hrdinová
Eva Hrdinová.description:
Eva Hrdinová is a Czech tennis player.
Hrdinová has won three singles and 18 doubles titles on the ITF tour in her career. On 14 April 2008, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 168. Wikipedia

David Prinosil.label: David Prinosil
David Prinosil.description:
David Prinosil is a former tennis player from Germany, who turned professional in 1991.
Prinosil was born in Olomouc, Czechoslovakia, but later moved to Germany. Wikipedia

Doris Hart.label: Doris Hart
Doris Hart.description:
Doris Hart is a former World No. 1 American female tennis player.
As a child, she suffered from osteomyelitis, which resulted in a permanently impaired right leg. Wikipedia
Doris Hart.Born: June 20, 1925 (age 88), St. Louis, Missouri, United States

Guy Forget.label: Guy Forget
Guy Forget.description: Guy Forget is a French former professional tennis player. During his career, he helped France win the Davis Cup in both 1991 and 1996. Since retiring as a player, he has served as France's Davis Cup team captain. Wikipedia

Goran Ivanišević.label: Goran Ivanisevic
Goran Ivanišević.description: Goran Ivanišević is a retired Croatian professional tennis player. He is the only person to win the men's singles title at Wimbledon as a wildcard. Wikipedia

Denis Gremelmayr.label: Denis Gremelmayr
Denis Gremelmayr.description: Denis Gremelmayr is a German male tennis player. Gremelmayr turned pro in 2000 and reached #97 in August, 2006. He spent 2007 in the top 200 and finished the year at #119. His career high ranking is #59, achieved on May 5, 2008. Wikipedia

František Čermák.label: František Čermák
František Čermák.description: František Čermák is a Czech professional tennis player. He has won 28 doubles titles on the ATP Tour, and has been a finalist 20 times. He achieved a career-high doubles ranking of World No. 14 in February 2010. Wikipedia

Dorothy Cheney.label: Dorothy Cheney
Dorothy Cheney.description: Dorothy “Dodo” Bundy Cheney is the daughter of Tennis Hall of Famer May Sutton Bundy and U.S. doubles champion Tom Bundy. She has been an outstanding American tennis player from her youth into her 90s. Wikipedia
Dorothy Cheney.Born: September 1, 1916 (age 97), Los Angeles, California, United States

Elena Baltacha.label: Elena Baltacha
Elena Baltacha.description: Elena Sergeevna Baltacha is a former British professional tennis player of Ukrainian background. Being a four-time winner of the Aegon Award, she was also a long-term British No. 1, a position she held intermittently from 2002 to 2012. Wikipedia

Florian Mayer.label: Florian Mayer
Florian Mayer.description:
Florian Mayer is a German professional tennis player. He plays on both the ATP Tour and the Challenger Tour.
Mayer reached his career-high singles ranking of World No. 18 in June 2011. Wikipedia

Ellsworth Vines.label: Henry Vines
Ellsworth Vines.description: Henry Ellsworth Vines, Jr. was an American tennis champion of the 1930s, the World No. 1 player or the co-No. 1 for four years in 1932, 1935, 1936 and 1937, able to win Pro Slam titles on three different surfaces. Wikipedia
Ellsworth Vines.Born: September 28, 1911, Los Angeles, California, United States
Ellsworth Vines.Died: March 17, 1994, La Quinta, California, United States

Fabio Fognini.label: Fabio Fognini
Fabio Fognini.description: Fabio Fognini is a professional tennis player and the current Italian No. 1. His career-high singles ranking is World No. 14, which he achieved in February 2014. Wikipedia

Illya Marchenko.label: Illya Marchenko
Illya Marchenko.description: Illya Marchenko is a Ukrainian male tennis player. Marchenko turned professional in 2005 and had been playing at the Futures and Challengers level from 2005–2008. His career high in singles is #67 and he is inactive in doubles. Wikipedia

Fred Perry.label: Fred Perry
Fred Perry.description: Frederick John "Fred" Perry was a championship-winning English tennis and table tennis player who won 10 Majors including eight Grand Slams and two Pro Slams. Wikipedia

Irina-Camelia Begu.label: Irina-Camelia Begu
Irina-Camelia Begu.description: Irina-Camelia Begu is a professional Romanian tennis player. On 12 September 2011, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 38. Her highest doubles ranking of 35 was reached on 30 July 2012. She is coached by Marius Comănescu. Wikipedia

Don Budge.label: Don Budge
Don Budge.description: John Donald Budge was an American tennis champion who was a World No. 1 player for five years, first as an amateur and then as a professional. Wikipedia
Awards: Associated Press Male Athlete of the Year

Ivan Ljubičić.label: Ivan Ljubičić
Ivan Ljubičić.description:
Ivan Ljubičić is a retired Croatian tennis player. His career-high ATP singles ranking was World No. 3.
Tall and powerfully built, he was noted for his strong serve and fluid groundstrokes. Wikipedia
Ivan Ljubičić.Born: March 19, 1979 (age 35), Banja Luka, Bosnia and Herzegovina

Iva Majoli.label: Iva Majoli
Iva Majoli.description: Iva Majoli Marić is a former professional tennis player from Croatia. She upset Martina Hingis to win the women's singles title at the French Open in 1997. Majoli also won eight singles titles and one women's doubles title during her career. Wikipedia

Corinna Dentoni.label: Corinna Dentoni
Corinna Dentoni.description: Corinna Dentoni is a professional Italian tennis player. Her highest WTA singles ranking is 132, which she reached on June 22, 2009. Her career-high in doubles is 151, which she reached on May 25, 2009. Wikipedia

Jérémy Chardy.label: Jérémy Chardy
Jérémy Chardy.description: Jérémy Chardy is a French professional tennis player. He has won one singles title at Stuttgart in 2009, reached the quarterfinals of the 2013 Australian Open and achieved a career-high singles ranking of World No. 25 in January 2013. Wikipedia

Elizabeth Ryan.label: Elizabeth Ryan
Elizabeth Ryan.description: Elizabeth Montague Ryan was an American tennis player who was born in Anaheim, California but lived most of her life in the United Kingdom. Ryan won 30 Grand Slam titles. Wikipedia

Jarkko Nieminen.label: Jarkko Nieminen
Jarkko Nieminen.description:
Jarkko Kalervo Nieminen is a Finnish professional tennis player.
His highest ranking is World No. 13, achieved in July 2006. He has won two ATP singles titles and three doubles titles in his career. Wikipedia

Frederico Gil.label: Frederico Gil
Frederico Gil.description: Frederico Gil is a Portuguese professional tennis player who competes on the ATP Tour. In April 2011, he achieved a career-high singles ranking of World No. 62, the highest ranking a Portuguese player ... Wikipedia

Horia Tecău.label: Horia Tecău
Horia Tecău.description: Horia Tecău is a Romanian tennis player who turned pro in 2003, and is a doubles specialist. His career-high doubles ranking is World No. 5, achieved in August 2012. Wikipedia

Harel Levy.label: Harel Levy
Harel Levy.description: Harel Levy is a retired Israeli professional male tennis player. He reached the final of the 2000 Toronto Masters and achieved a career-high singles ranking of World No. 30, with his best doubles ranking being World No. 71 in May 2008. Wikipedia

Horacio Zeballos.label: Horacio Zeballos
Horacio Zeballos.description: Horacio Zeballos, Jr. is a professional Argentine tennis player on the men's circuit. His career-high singles ranking is world no. 39, which he achieved in March 2013. His highest doubles ranking to date has been world no. 32, in October 2010. Wikipedia

Dudi Sela.label: Dudi Sela
Dudi Sela.description:
David "Dudi" Sela is an Israeli professional tennis player.
Sela reached a career-high singles ranking of World No. 29 in July 2009. He is currently Israel's top men's singles player, ahead of Amir Weintraub. Wikipedia

Conor Niland.label: Conor Niland
Conor Niland.description: Conor Niland is a former Irish professional tennis player. He was born in Birmingham, England, and grew up in Limerick, Ireland. Wikipedia

Frank Sedgman.label: Frank Sedgman
Frank Sedgman.description: Francis "Frank" Arthur Sedgman, AM is a retired former World No. 1 amateur tennis champion. In his 1979 autobiography Jack Kramer, the long-time tennis promoter and great player himself, included Sedgman ... Wikipedia

Jaroslav Pospíšil.label: Jaroslav Pospíšil
Jaroslav Pospíšil.description: Jaroslav Pospíšil is a Czech tennis player playing on the ITF Futures Tour and ATP Challenger Tour. On May 23, 2011, he reached his highest ATP singles ranking of World No. 103. Wikipedia

Jack Crawford (tennis).label: Jack Crawford
Jack Crawford (tennis).description:
John Herbert Crawford was an Australian tennis player during the 1930s. He was the World No. 1 player for 1933.
Crawford was born in Urangeline, near Albury, New South Wales. Wikipedia

Karl Meiler.label: Karl Meiler
Karl Meiler.description:
Karl Meiler is a former tennis player from West Germany.
Meiler won four singles and seventeen doubles titles during his professional career. The German reached his highest singles ATP-ranking on 23 August 1973, when he became World No. 20. Wikipedia

Karina Habšudová.label: Karina Habšudová
Karina Habšudová.description:
Karina Habšudová is a former Slovak female professional tennis player. She has been ranked as high as 10 in the world. Together with Karol Kučera she won the Hopman Cup in 1998.
She also had a successful junior career. Wikipedia

Karin Knapp.label: Karin Knapp
Karin Knapp.description: Karin Knapp is an Italian tennis player. Her career-high ranking was world no. 35, which she reached on 25 February 2008. Wikipedia

James Duckworth (tennis).label: James Duckworth
James Duckworth (tennis).description: James 'Jack' Duckworth is an Australian professional tennis player, reaching a career high ranking of 132, on 4 November 2013. He is the grandson of Beryl Penrose, who won the Australian Open singles and doubles titles in 1955. Wikipedia

Joshua Pim.label: Joshua Pim
Joshua Pim.description: Dr. Joshua Pim F.R.C.S.I was a medical doctor and a renowned former World No. 1 Irish amateur tennis player. He won the Wimbledon men's singles title two years in a row, in 1893 and 1894. Wikipedia

Coco Vandeweghe.label: Coco Vandeweghe
Coco Vandeweghe.description: Coco Vandeweghe is an American professional tennis player. She played on the junior circuit, where she reached a high ranking of junior world no. 15. She won the 2008 US Open Girls' singles championship. Wikipedia
Coco Vandeweghe.Born: December 6, 1991 (age 22), New York City, New York, United States

Karel Koželuh.label: Karel Koželuh
Karel Koželuh.description: Karel Koželuh, 7 March 1895 – 27 April 1950; Hungarian Kozeluh Károly; was a top Czech tennis, soccer, and ice hockey player of the 1920s and 1930s. Wikipedia

Denisa Chládková.label: Denisa Chládková
Denisa Chládková.description:
Denisa Chládková was a professional tennis player from the Czech Republic.
She did not win any WTA titles, but she is probably best remembered for reaching the Wimbledon quarterfinals in 1997, playing in only her third Grand Slam main draw. Wikipedia

Julie Halard-Decugis.label: Julie Halard-Decugis
Julie Halard-Decugis.description:
Julie Halard-Decugis is a former professional female tennis player.
Halard-Decugis lived in La Baule, France during the initial stages of her career and later moved to Pully, Switzerland. Wikipedia
Julie Halard-Decugis.Born: September 10, 1970 (age 43), Palace of Versailles, Versailles, France

Karol Beck.label: Karol Beck
Karol Beck.description: Karol Beck is a male tennis player from Slovakia, who turned professional in 2001. His career-high singles ranking is World No. 36, achieved in August 2005. Wikipedia

John Newcombe.label: John Newcombe
John Newcombe.description: John David Newcombe, AO, OBE is an Australian former world No. 1 tennis player who won seven Grand Slam singles titles, and an all-time record 17 doubles titles. Wikipedia
Books: The Power Within How to Create a High Performance Mind
Newk Life on and Off the Court

Kamil Čapkovič.label: Kamil Čapkovič
Kamil Čapkovič.description: Kamil Čapkovič is a professional Slovak tennis player. He was born in Michalovce, Slovak Republic. Wikipedia

Ken Skupski.label: Ken Skupski
Ken Skupski.description: Ken Skupski is an English professional tennis player who lives in Liverpool, England. He is best known as a doubles player, most successfully partnering Colin Fleming. Wikipedia

Heidi El Tabakh.label: Heidi El Tabakh
Heidi El Tabakh.description: Heidi El Tabakh is an Egyptian-born Canadian professional tennis player from Toronto, Ontario, Canada. Her highest WTA singles ranking is 146, which she reached on October 8, 2012. Wikipedia

Jonas Björkman.label: Jonas Björkman
Jonas Björkman.description: Jonas Lars Björkman is a former World No. 4 Swedish professional tennis player. He is also a former World No. 1 in doubles. Björkman retired from professional tennis after competing at the 2008 Tennis Masters Cup Doubles championships. Wikipedia

Kerry Reid.label: Kerry Reid
Kerry Reid.description: Kerry Melville Reid, MBE, is a former professional tennis player from Australia. During her 17-year career, Reid won one Grand Slam singles title and 26 other singles titles and was the runner-up in 40 singles tournaments. Wikipedia

Kathleen McKane Godfree.label: Kathleen McKane Godfree
Kathleen McKane Godfree.description:
Kathleen "Kitty" McKane Godfree was a British female tennis and badminton player.
According to Wallis Myers of The Daily Telegraph and the Daily Mail, Godfree was ranked in the world top ten from 1921 ... Wikipedia

John Doeg.label: John Doeg
John Doeg.description:
John Thomas Godfray Hope Doeg was a male tennis player from the United States.
He won one major singles tournament, the 1930 U.S. National Championships at Forrest Hills, defeating Frank Shields in the final in four sets. Wikipedia

Jack Sock.label: Jack Sock
Jack Sock.description: Jack Sock is an American tennis player. He won the 2011 US Open mixed doubles title with fellow American Melanie Oudin and the boys' junior US Open championship in 2010. Wikipedia

Kathrin Wörle.label: Kathrin Wörle-Scheller
Kathrin Wörle.description:
Kathrin Wörle-Scheller is a German tennis player.
Wörle-Scheller has won three singles and seven doubles titles on the ITF tour in her career. On 22 February 2010, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 119. Wikipedia

Klára Zakopalová.label: Klára Zakopalová
Klára Zakopalová.description: Klára Zakopalová is a professional Czech tennis player. She was born and still lives in Prague. Wikipedia

Hana Šromová.label: Hana Šromová
Hana Šromová.description: Hana Šromová is a former professional female tennis player from the Czech Republic. On June 19, 2006, Šromová achieved her career-high singles ranking World No. 87. On July 24, 2006, high doubles ranking World No. 63. Wikipedia

Jean-René Lisnard.label: Jean-René Lisnard
Jean-René Lisnard.description: Jean-René Lisnard is a professional tennis player who represents Monaco, and formerly France. He has been a member of the Monaco Davis Cup team since 2007. Wikipedia

Jan Kodeš.label: Jan Kodeš
Jan Kodeš.description:
Jan Kodeš is a right-handed Czech former tennis player who won three Grand Slam events in the early 1970s.
Kodeš's greatest success was on the clay courts of the French Open. Wikipedia

Johanna Larsson (tennis).label: Johanna Larsson
Johanna Larsson (tennis).description: Johanna Larsson is a Swedish tennis player. Her career-high ranking is world no. 46 achieved on 11 July 2011. Larsson has an impressive record on the ITF circuit, having never lost in a final. Wikipedia

Kei Nishikori.label: Kei Nishikori
Kei Nishikori.description: Kei Nishikori is a Japanese tennis player, currently ranked World No. 20 as of February 24, 2014. He began playing tennis at the age of five and qualified for his first ATP main draw event at the Countrywide Classic in Los Angeles at the age of 17. Wikipedia

Johan Brunström.label: Johan Brunström
Johan Brunström.description: Johan Brunström is a professional Swedish tennis player. His highest ATP doubles ranking is 31st, which he reached on 22 March 2010. His career high in singles is 377th, which he reached on 24 September 2007. Wikipedia

John Bromwich.label: John Bromwich
John Bromwich.description: John Edward Bromwich was a male tennis player from Australia who, along with his countryman Vivian McGrath, was one of the first great players to use a two-handed backhand. Wikipedia

Juan Mónaco.label: Juan Mónaco
Juan Mónaco.description: Juan Mónaco, nicknamed "Pico", is a male tennis player from Argentina. He has won eight singles titles and reached a career-high singles ranking of World No. 10 in July 2012. Wikipedia

Jasmin Wöhr.label: Jasmin Wöhr
Jasmin Wöhr.description:
Jasmin Wöhr is a retired German tennis player. She turned professional in 1999 before retiring in 2012.
Wöhr was part of the Germany Fed Cup team in 2006. She was an active competitor on both the WTA Tour and ITF circuit. Wikipedia

Jesse Huta Galung.label: Jesse Huta Galung
Jesse Huta Galung.description: Jesse Huta Galung is a professional Dutch tennis player. Wikipedia

Jaroslav Levinský.label: Jaroslav Levinský
Jaroslav Levinský.description: Jaroslav Levinský is a professional doubles tennis player from the Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Angela Mortimer.label: Angela Mortimer
Angela Mortimer.description: Florence Angela Margaret Mortimer Barrett is a former World No. 1 British female tennis player. She was born in Plymouth, Devon, England. She is married to the veteran BBC commentator John Barrett. Wikipedia
Nominations: BBC Sports Personality of the Year Award
